Text.Value: Why did you attack?
What happened to Dribbles the Clown?
The greatest honour... of them all.
I saw in your eyes... what I see in my own... death.
Where is Dribbles' corpse?
Leave.
What's the Tribunal?
It is 'His will'? Who are you talking about?
You singled me out from the crowd. Why?
I killed him... bathed in his blood... a death worthy of the list... of the Tribunal.
Mistress needed his body parts... for her art...
What type of creature are you?
*You feel a rush of power, dark and insidious - something prevents the corpse from answering.*
To sow chaos... it is His will...
I am called... Fumm...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Who are you?
A shapechanger... people call us... doppelgangers...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*

Synopsis: The SwD dialog for the doppelganger who has shape-changed to look like a beloved Dribbles the Clown. While dead, the doppelganger is in his real form though.
